It's you!

271
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:48,374
♪

272
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:49,609
(metal scraping)

273
00:11:49,609 --> 00:11:51,978
Captain, we're on the sandbar!

274
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:55,014
Good, this will work out fine.

275
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:59,519
Get us on land.

276
00:11:59,519 --> 00:12:01,187
Retreat!

277
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:03,189
(squawking)

278
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:13,299
♪

279
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:16,836
Oh, something
smells scrumptious!

280
00:12:16,836 --> 00:12:18,905
Wieners, my favorite!

281
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:20,406
Sure looks good!

282
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:22,575
Dinner tonight is on the house!

283
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:27,113
♪

284
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:30,450
(sighing)

285
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:33,686
Genki, you hurt, 'Chi?

286
00:12:33,686 --> 00:12:37,223
No, I'm fine.

287
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:39,559
Cheer up, 'Chi!

288
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,793
Whatever.

289
00:12:40,793 --> 00:12:43,429
I'm sorry, Captain, it's all
our fault for dragging you

290
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:45,164
into this mess.

291
00:12:45,164 --> 00:12:46,633
What do you mean?

292
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:49,936
She means Moo is going to
come after you two as well.

293
00:12:49,936 --> 00:12:53,573
No problem, I don't care
who my customers are.

294
00:12:53,573 --> 00:12:55,942
As long as I get
my money in the end,

295
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:58,378
I'll get you
to your destination.

296
00:12:58,378 --> 00:13:00,146
Genki, Mocchi!

297
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:01,514
Dinner's on!

298
00:13:01,514 --> 00:13:04,317
Food, 'Chi, 'Chi!

299
00:13:04,317 --> 00:13:05,385
Come eat!

300
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:07,353
No, thanks, you go.

301
00:13:07,353 --> 00:13:10,223
'Chi?

302
00:13:10,223 --> 00:13:11,424
You did good back there.

303
00:13:11,424 --> 00:13:12,425
Huh?

304
00:13:12,425 --> 00:13:14,794
Thanks, what's wrong?

305
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:16,095
How come you're
sitting out here?

306
00:13:16,095 --> 00:13:17,664
Nothing.

307
00:13:17,664 --> 00:13:22,035
Hey, you still mad 'cause I was
treating you like a kid before?

308
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:23,903
Then I apologize.

309
00:13:23,903 --> 00:13:27,140
I don't need your apologies.

310
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,342
Maybe Captain Jim was right,

311
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:31,377
maybe I am just
a self‐centered kid

312
00:13:31,377 --> 00:13:34,314
who always winds up getting
my friends into trouble.

313
00:13:34,314 --> 00:13:38,384
You're thinking about
things a little too much.

314
00:13:38,384 --> 00:13:40,586
When I was your age I did
a lot of foolish things,

315
00:13:40,586 --> 00:13:43,222
and I got my friends into
quite a bit of trouble.

316
00:13:43,222 --> 00:13:44,390
Did you really?

317
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:47,060
Sure, I was cocky and
I used to charge around

318
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:48,895
like some kind of loose cannon,

319
00:13:48,895 --> 00:13:51,364
nothing could stop me,
I wasn't afraid of anything.

320
00:13:51,364 --> 00:13:52,899
Like me?

321
00:13:52,899 --> 00:13:55,802
Yup, but because
I was like that

322
00:13:55,802 --> 00:13:58,738
I learned a lot
of lessons, Genki.

323
00:13:58,738 --> 00:14:01,507
People can learn a lot
from their past mistakes.

324
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,744
Important things, things
that make them stronger.

325
00:14:04,744 --> 00:14:08,915
You mean, I could grow up
to be strong like you?

326
00:14:08,915 --> 00:14:10,717
So when any baddies
come to get me,

327
00:14:10,717 --> 00:14:13,419
I'll be able to blow
them out of the water!

328
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:14,954
That's the attitude!

329
00:14:14,954 --> 00:14:18,024
Keep that up, and you'll
be much stronger than me.

330
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:20,293
Well, I've got to get a move
on and make some mistakes,

331
00:14:20,293 --> 00:14:22,061
so I can start learning!

332
00:14:22,061 --> 00:14:23,996
That's not quite what I meant.

333
00:14:23,996 --> 00:14:26,399
(laughing together)

334
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:29,068
Ah, Genki's happy again.

335
00:14:29,068 --> 00:14:30,503
'Chi!

336
00:14:30,503 --> 00:14:35,842
♪

337
00:14:35,842 --> 00:14:37,944
Everything's ready!

338
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:40,279
Right, let's do it, gang!

339
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:42,281
Yeah!

340
00:14:42,281 --> 00:14:44,283
(grunting)

341
00:14:44,283 --> 00:14:46,285
♪

342
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:47,920
You're such a wimp, Golem.

343
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,222
Can't you help us?

344
00:14:49,222 --> 00:14:50,323
(whimpering)

345
00:14:50,323 --> 00:14:56,629
♪

346
00:14:56,629 --> 00:14:57,630
Eared Mew!

347
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,899
Yes, sir, starting the engine.

348
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:03,202
(engine winding up)

349
00:15:03,202 --> 00:15:06,172
Now, let's get out of here
before those crawfish come back.

350
00:15:06,172 --> 00:15:07,407
You said it!

351
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:11,677
♪

352
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:13,813
Rock, move out!

353
00:15:17,784 --> 00:15:20,853
Keep the speed up,
we've almost made it!

354
00:15:20,853 --> 00:15:21,954
I hear you!

355
00:15:21,954 --> 00:15:23,956
(rushing water)

356
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:28,828
♪

357
00:15:28,828 --> 00:15:30,463
‐They're here!
‐Ready!

358
00:15:30,463 --> 00:15:32,598
‐Me too.
‐Don't let them near the boat!

359
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:35,435
‐Right!
‐(grunt)

360
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:36,869
‐Where are they?
‐Look!

361
00:15:36,869 --> 00:15:38,671
They went into
deeper water!

362
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:41,374
We've got to pass by them
to make it to the other side.

363
00:15:41,374 --> 00:15:44,710
(whimpering)

364
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:48,614
Come on, Raspberry, don't
let those baddies get ya!

365
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,683
(crash)

366
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:54,454
♪

367
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:57,723
(groaning)

368
00:15:57,723 --> 00:16:00,760
Everyone, jump in the river!

369
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,562
Golem not know how to swim!

370
00:16:02,562 --> 00:16:05,832
Do you want to go down
with the ship then?

371
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:08,534
If you can't swim,
use the harpoon floats.

372
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:10,536
The rest of you try
to swim to shore.

373
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:11,637
What about you?

374
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:13,639
I'm staying right
here with my ferry.

375
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,975
You can't do that,
it's going down!

376
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,344
Not if I can help it!

377
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:21,080
‐Don't stay!
‐Get going!

378
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:24,150
(grunting)

379
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:28,120
(whimpering)

380
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,188
Eared Mew!

381
00:16:31,257 --> 00:16:34,393
‐Look after our passengers.
‐Aye, aye!

382
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:41,033
♪

383
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:43,169
(creaking)

384
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:45,705
No!

385
00:16:45,705 --> 00:16:47,707
(splashing)

386
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:49,709
(squawking)

387
00:16:49,709 --> 00:16:57,583
♪

388
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,452
We don't stand a
chance against them.

389
00:16:59,452 --> 00:17:01,420
Keep swimming
as fast as you can!

390
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,256
No, Jim!

391
00:17:03,256 --> 00:17:05,258
(squawking)

392
00:17:05,258 --> 00:17:07,159
♪

393
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:09,161
(bubbling)

394
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:13,165
♪

395
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:14,433
What?

396
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:16,168
(groaning)

397
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:18,371
(crash)

398
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:19,505
Jim!

399
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:26,979
♪

400
00:17:26,979 --> 00:17:28,881
Answer if you can hear us!

401
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:30,216
Jim?

402
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:31,984
Are you there?

403
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:33,352
Captain?

404
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:34,620
(grunting)

405
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:37,089
We've been searching
for the captain for hours

406
00:17:37,089 --> 00:17:38,858
and still no sign of him.

407
00:17:38,858 --> 00:17:40,826
Captain.

408
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:41,861
(crying)

409
00:17:41,861 --> 00:17:45,197
Can't be, he must be there!

410
00:17:45,197 --> 00:17:49,101
Hey, Jim, yo!

411
00:17:49,101 --> 00:17:50,836
Hey, Jim!

412
00:17:50,836 --> 00:17:52,838
(glittering metallic sound)

413
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:58,511
♪

414
00:17:58,511 --> 00:18:01,948
I'm not that easy to get rid of.

415
00:18:01,948 --> 00:18:03,983
I got caught
in the down current.

416
00:18:03,983 --> 00:18:08,621
I had a long ways to walk back,
so it took me quite a while.

417
00:18:08,621 --> 00:18:09,989
Captain?

418
00:18:09,989 --> 00:18:11,190
Jim?

419
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:13,526
You know, you people sure
got your money's worth today.

420
00:18:13,526 --> 00:18:15,795
‐Jim!
‐Captain!

421
00:18:15,795 --> 00:18:18,598
Okay, that's enough,
what's gotten into you guys?

422
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:20,900
(laughing)

423
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:25,371
♪

424
00:18:25,371 --> 00:18:27,306
You sure overreacted.

425
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:29,308
(laughing)

426
00:18:29,308 --> 00:18:36,616
♪

427
00:18:36,616 --> 00:18:38,484
(wind blowing)

428
00:18:38,484 --> 00:18:42,188
♪

429
00:18:42,188 --> 00:18:44,190
This job would be so much easier

430
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:47,259
if we could just use
the humans to do the work.

431
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,595
Master Moo said he didn't want
to go to all that trouble,

432
00:18:49,595 --> 00:18:51,063
so stop your whining.

433
00:18:51,063 --> 00:18:54,300
You said it, brother, and
anyway, the job's almost done.

434
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:58,504
♪

435
00:18:58,504 --> 00:19:00,206
That's impossible.

436
00:19:00,206 --> 00:19:06,412
♪

437
00:19:06,412 --> 00:19:07,780
Oh!

438
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:10,616
♪

439
00:19:10,616 --> 00:19:12,618
(deep growling)

440
00:19:12,618 --> 00:19:15,054
♪

441
00:19:15,054 --> 00:19:19,592
No, I can't believe
what I'm seeing.

442
00:19:19,592 --> 00:19:21,694
That's Moo's original body!

443
00:19:21,694 --> 00:19:25,531
♪

444
00:19:25,531 --> 00:19:27,466
You folks take care now.

445
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:29,869
Thanks, I really hope
we see you again.

446
00:19:29,869 --> 00:19:31,003
Sure!

447
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:33,839
Bye!

448
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,676
Captain, I hate to
bring this up but‐‐

449
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:38,477
What do we owe
you for the boat?

450
00:19:38,477 --> 00:19:41,247
Don't worry about it,
I'll build another one.

451
00:19:41,247 --> 00:19:44,850
(deep sigh)

452
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:48,020
Genki, I'm not good at goodbyes,

453
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,556
so why don't we just go
our own separate ways?

454
00:19:50,556 --> 00:19:52,458
Um, Jim...

455
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:53,426
Yeah?

456
00:19:53,426 --> 00:19:55,761
Do you think we'll ever
see each other again?

457
00:19:55,761 --> 00:19:58,798
♪

458
00:19:58,798 --> 00:20:03,169
Hm, of course, we will,
we're friends after all!

459
00:20:03,169 --> 00:20:07,406
(chuckling)

460
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:08,774
We're friends, 'Chi!

461
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:11,143
That's right, friends!

462
00:20:11,143 --> 00:20:13,412
Then I'll see you
when I see you!

463
00:20:13,412 --> 00:20:15,548
‐Hey, what for us!
‐'Chi!

464
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:17,483
‐Well, thanks again!
‐Take care.

465
00:20:17,483 --> 00:20:18,617
Bye!

466
00:20:18,617 --> 00:20:22,988
♪

467
00:20:22,988 --> 00:20:25,057
Genki cry, 'Chi?

468
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:28,994
I'm sweating, all right,
haven't you seen sweat before?

469
00:20:28,994 --> 00:20:30,129
Oh.

470
00:20:30,129 --> 00:20:31,997
♪

471
00:20:31,997 --> 00:20:34,600
(laughing)

472
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,702
Come on, guys,
we've got work to do!

473
00:20:36,702 --> 00:20:39,505
Let's go and find that Phoenix!

474
00:20:39,505 --> 00:20:40,706
Yeah!

475
00:20:40,706 --> 00:20:42,908
(laughing)

476
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:45,478
♪

477
00:20:47,046 --> 00:20:48,114
♪ Monsters ♪

478
00:20:48,114 --> 00:20:49,515
♪ Monster's rule ♪

479
00:20:49,515 --> 00:21:14,273
♪

480
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,808
♪ Monsters rule ♪

